arStrings.szText: Ack, spiritborn? We are Kehjistani, you were raised in the Zakarum faith.
Confused, but not angry. Just wants to understand.
I dream of Umbaru, I see myself there. I've not turned my back on Akarat, just seeing his light through a new lens.
Calmly explaining. Really wants his father to understand, but isn't angry or forceful. You can hear the happiness in his voice as he shares his perspective.
I speak of heritage. The one that is within you as it is in your mother. Give me time. Your mother more so. We will come to terms with this.
Sighing. Fatherly and caring. Tired, but knowing.
